# Whitelist .gitignore for the HAMMER2 Windows port.
#
# Policy: track ONLY source files (*.c / *.h) and the build configuration
# (CMakeLists.txt, Makefile).  Everything else -- build output, test images,
# binaries, man pages, stray files -- is ignored.
#
# How it works: rule 1 ignores everything; rule 2 lets git descend into
# subdirectories; the "!" rules re-include the file types we want; the final
# section re-ignores generated build directories.  Later patterns win.

# 1. Ignore everything by default.
*

# 2. ...but allow git to descend into subdirectories to find the files below.
!*/

# 3. Source files.
!*.c
!*.h

# 4. Build system / configuration.
!CMakeLists.txt
!Makefile
!*.cmake.in
!*.mk

# 5. Project documentation / metadata.
!README.md
!*.md
!LICENSE
!.gitignore

# 6. Generated build output -- never track (overrides the includes above for
#    anything inside these directories).
build/
build_cmake/
out/
cmake-build-*/

# 7. Belt-and-suspenders: common build artifacts and large/test files, in case
#    a build is ever run in-tree rather than under build/.
*.obj
*.o
*.exe
*.dll
*.lib
*.exp
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.idb
*.res
*.manifest
*.img
*.iso
